  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-10-15",
    "date": "2022-05-19T11:30:27Z",
    "text": "Countering China Economic Coercion Act\n\nThis bill establishes an interagency task force to respond to the Chinese government's acts of economic coercion.\n\nThe task force must oversee the development and implementation of an integrated U.S. government strategy to respond to such acts of economic coercion. The strategy must include an evaluation of the costs such acts have on U.S. businesses and economic performance.\n\nThe task force must also report to Congress on the strategy as well as a comprehensive review on the economic tools that the Chinese government uses (or can use) to coerce other governments, non-Chinese companies, and multilateral institutions and organizations."
  },
